data.name: label20.Text
data.value: You can also choose to skip activation at this time and use the Cricut DesignStudio in trial mode. Trial mode only allows you to cut with the cartridges that came with your Cricut machine. So, with the Cricut Personal Cutter you can only cut using the "George and Basic Shapes" cartridge, with the Cricut Expression you can only cut using the "Plantin SchoolBook" and "Accent Essentials" cartridges, and with the Cricut Create you can only cut using the "DonJuan" cartridge.

data.name: label24.Text
data.value: If you choose not to activate by phone at this time you can go back to the "Activate using the Internet" screen or you can skip activation and use the Cricut DesignStudio in trial mode. Remember that trial mode only allows you to cut with the cartridges that came with your Cricut machine.

data.name: label52.Text
data.value: Before you call to activate this copy of the Cricut DesignStudio by phone, you will need to have some information ready. The technician you speak with will ask you for your six-part serial number and for the number displayed in the box below labeled "Registration Code". He or she will then give you a number consisting of eight parts of four letters or numbers each, which you will type into the boxes labeled "Activation Key".

data.name: label8.Text
data.value: This copy of the Cricut DesignStudio software is currently running in Trial Mode. If you purchased this copy of the software and have a serial number, please enter it in the following six boxes labeled "Serial Number". Your serial number should have six parts of six letters or numbers each separated by a '-' (dash). Please enter each of the six parts into its own box. You may also enter your name and email address to personally register this copy of the software.

data.name: label64.Text
data.value: Your Cricut machine must be running the latest version of its built-in software (called "firmware") to be compatible with the Cricut Design Studio PC software. Please follow these instructions to update your Cricut machine. The update process will take 5-10 minutes and once the process begins it is very important to allow it to finish without interruption.

data.name: label66.Text
data.value: STEP 4 - Click the "Begin Updating Now" button to start the updating process. Remember, you must allow this process to run completely before shutting down this program or turning off this computer or your Cricut machine.

data.name: label16.ToolTip
data.value:
Click and drag the slider to increase or decrease the default size in 1/8" increments.
Or click on the tick marks to the right or left of the slider to change size by 1/8, 1/4, 1/2, 1, or 2" with each click.

data.name: label69.Text
data.value: STEP 2 - On the Cricut machine, hold down the STOP button (keep it held down) and press the power button. After about 5 seconds the Cricut will beep once. This is the signal that the Cricut machine is ready to be updated. You may now release the STOP button.

data.name: label32.Text
data.value: If this computer is not connected to the Internet click the "Activate by phone" button. This screen will change to provide additonal instructions for activating by phone. Don't worry, you won't lose any of the information you have already entered.

data.name: label70.Text
data.value: STEP 1 - Make sure your Cricut machine is turned off and connected to this computer using a proper USB cable. See the "Getting Started" documention for instructions on connecting the USB cable if necessary.

data.name: label71.Text
data.value: PLEASE NOTE that some Cricut machines may require two passes to fully complete the update. So, after the first update finishes a message may appear asking you to perform a second update, starting over from Step 1. Please follow all instructions carefully.
